The Telegraph - Calcutta
 Saturday, March 22, 2003 				Metro Recommends
				 																The Show				 																																	(G.D. Birla Sabhagar, March 22, 6.30 pm)				 																																	lEnjoy an evening of classical music with Pandit Shiv Kumar Sharma (picture above) on the santoor and Kumar Bose on the tabla. Governor Viren J. Shah will inaugurate the show, organised by Vijay Kichlu. The Ashram will hold regular classes on Indian classical music for students from the financially weaker section of society 				 																The Book				 																																	(Medha M. Kudaisya)				 																																	lThis book goes beyond being just a biography, although of a prominent Indian who had a hand in shaping the country through his own successes, deeds and ideas. It is the backdrop of a century spanning two World Wars, the Indian freedom struggle and independence that provide the material for an epic story				 																The Match (March 23, 1.30 pm, Sony Max) lDont miss Souravs boys in  blue battling it out against defending champion Australia  in the title match of the 2003 World Cup at the Wanderers  in Johannesburg on Sunday  The CD				 																																	(Bob Dylan)				 																																	lThis Dylan classic is now available on CD. An absolute must in the definitive collection of works by folk-rock icon, this set comprises some of the master lyricists most outstanding songs, like Tangled Up In Blue, Idiot Wind and Shelter From The Storm
